</li> 
<li class="comment byuser comment-author-warded-man odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-350889">
<article id="comment-350889" class="comment-body">
<footer class="comment-meta">
<div class="comment-author vcard"><img src="http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/bc2bc766ed17714b93bc782fd441a2fd?s=50&#038;d=mm&#038;r=pg" width="50" height="50" alt="" class="avatar avatar-50wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-50 alignnone photo avatar-default"/><span class="fn"><b>Warded Man</b> <br/><br/><a href="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/ti-index/ti-vol-2-chapter-2-3/#comment-350889"><time datetime="2016-05-16T21:38:12+00:00"> May 16, 2016 at 9:38 pm</time></a></span></div> </footer> 
<div class="comment-content">
<p>I think he means more of a Footnote at the end of the chapter rather than an annotation. I got the reference but I&#8217;ve seen plenty of footnotes at the end of pages or chapters of other translated works. </p>
<p>Also I really want to change “The timer… starts!” to &#8220;The timer starts&#8230;.NOW!&#8221;. Small difference but the first version is a little awkward.</p>
</div> 
